properties.headline: Winter Storm Warning issued January 10 at 1:58PM CST until January 12 at 6:00AM CST by NWS Milwaukee/Sullivan WI
properties.description:
...COMPLEX WINTER STORM TO IMPACT THE REGION...

* WHAT...Snow this evening into Saturday night, heavy at times
later Saturday into Saturday night. Snow of 2 to 4 inches
tonight into Saturday morning, and then 4 to 7 inches Saturday
afternoon into Saturday night. Storm totals will be in the 6 to
10 inch range. In addition to the snow, strong winds gusts of 35
to 45 mph will cause blowing and drifting of the snow throughout
much of the event. Gusts could reach as high as 50 mph Saturday
afternoon and evening.

* WHERE...Fond du Lac, Sheboygan and Dodge Counties.

* WHEN...For the Winter Storm Warning, from noon Saturday to 6
AM CST Sunday. For the Winter Weather Advisory, from 8 PM this
evening to noon CST Saturday.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be very difficult. Areas of blowing
snow could significantly reduce visibility. Gusty winds could
bring down tree branches.
properties.instruction:
If you must travel, keep an extra flashlight, food, and water in
your vehicle in case of an emergency.

Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.
